\f0\b\fs54 \cf0 Shrimp with Cocktail Sauce\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs34 \cf2 Serves:  
\b0 \cf0 6 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs46 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 lemon\
{\listtext	\'95	}Kosher salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 pounds large shrimp in the shell (about 30)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chili-sauce/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chili sauce}} (recommended: Heinz)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup ketchup (recommended: Heinz)\
{\listtext	\'95	}3 tablespoons prepared {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/horseradish/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 horseradish}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons fresh {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/lemon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 lemon juice}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 teaspoon hot sauce (recommended: Tabasco)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs46 \cf0 Cut the lemon in half and add it to a large pot of boiling salted water. Add the shrimp and cook, uncovered, for only 3 minutes, until the shrimp are just cooked through. Remove with a slotted spoon to a bowl of cool water. When the shrimp are cool enough to handle, peel and devein them. Keep cold until ready to serve.\
For the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cocktail-sauce/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cocktail sauce}}, combine the chili sauce, ketchup, horseradish, lemon juice, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/worcestershire-sauce/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Worcestershire sauce}}, and hot sauce. Serve with the shrimp.\
